            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Not Satisfied with the current teaching techniques & so called no curriculum theme of this institute, due to which I transferred my daughter post nursery class in a better preschool, the team deployed are into branded product type mode, where the behavioral changes can be seen from this year.\n\nWith Real Disappointment from My Side, A big NO & not recommended at all to those who are looking good education with their children on ground reality.\n\nMy Best Wishes to Self Declared \"Branded Institute\" to grow really on Ground rather on Papers !!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Mindseed Preschool & Daycare - Kalwa - Kalwan"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Pravin Patil"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-03-30",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Thank you Mindseed!!!\n\nWe enrolled our daughter Sanvi to Mindseed preschool  around 1.5 years back i.e. in Oct 2021.\nShe has completed playgroup and nursery(pre k) courses with the school. We are very much satisfied with her progress and we appreciate all the efforts put by Mindseed staff over these years.\n\nWe were bit hesitant initially to put our daughter into school as she was jusr 2 years old then, but Tasdik mam(Principal) ensured all the things a kid requires are in place from the word go. Our daughter started liking to go to school . She liked the environment and  we could see improvement in her day by day.\n\nWe would like to special mention and appreciate efforts of Nirmala Teacher , she has been very caring and supportive towards all the kids. Nirmala teacher goes beyond and make sure every kid in her batch is handled and groomed carefully. She gives motherly touch to young ones. Thanks to Heena mam as well for her support and guidance to our daughter in initial days.\n\nAnother good thing about mindseed was they ask regular feedback from parents and make sure their queries/concerns are resolved in timely manner.\n\nApart from curriculum , mindseed staff has organised various events like sports day, picnic day, annual day. All the preparations and executions of those events were commendable .Staff has really put their efforts in bring the best out from the kids.\n\nwe will surely recommend Mindseed pre school to other kids in area. And wish all the best for Mindseed staff to achieve their goals and mission.\n\nThanks and Regards ,\nDipali and Pravin Patil - Parents of Sanvi Patil (Pre K)",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
